c: 7
v: 49
t: "And pointing to the dwellers of the Garden, they will say, \"Are these not the people about whom you used to swear that Allah will never bestow His Grace upon them? They are entering the Garden where there will be no fear or grief.\" (They will make it clear that the Divine Law favors no particular peoples. Obeying His Laws brings His Grace and Bounties\"). Follow His Laws and, \"Enter the paradise of your own making, the society where there shall be no fear nor grief"